ries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":12,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Friskeny was born in 1370, in Kirton, Lincolnshire, England, her father, John Friskeny, was 26 and her mother, Mrs. Friskeny, was 22. She had at least 7 sons with Anthony Coney. She died in 1430, in her hometown, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1370–1430":"1370–1430","1375–1435":"1375–1435","1364–Male":"1364–Surnud","1368–Male":"1368–Surnud","1397–1456":"1397–1456","1399–Male":"1399–Surnud","1401–Male":"1401–Surnud","1402–Male":"1402–Surnud","1420–1466":"1420–1466","1344–1414":"1344–1414","1349–1370":"1349–1370","after 1370":"pärast 1370","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1349":"1349","1414":"1414","1369":"1369","1402":"1402","1435":"1435","1401":"1401","1456":"1456","1368":"1368","1466":"1466","1344":"1344","1399":"1399","about 1402":"umbes 1402","1420":"1420","1397":"1397","13990000":"1399","1430":"1430","1364":"1364","1375":"1375","about 1401":"umbes 1401","Kirton, Lincolnshire, England":"Kirton, Lincolnshire, England",",, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Lincoln, Lincoln, England":"Lincoln, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"England"},"fi":{"1370–1430":"1370–1430","1375–1435":"1375–1435","1364–Male":"1364–Kuollut","1368–Male":"1368–Kuollut","1397–1456":"1397–1456","1399–Male":"1399–Kuollut","1401–Male":"1